<figureCitation box="[697,838,740,764]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[143,210,1423,1445]" captionTargetBox="[143,1099,173,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-6@7.[143,1103,169,1387]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Scymnomorphus isolateralis sp. nov., (A) abdomen; (B–E) male genitalia: (B) penis, (C) apex of penis, (D) tegmen, lateral view, (E) tegmen, ventral view; (F–J) Scymnomorphus japonicus (Reitter), (F) abdomen; (G–J) male genitalia: (G) penis; (H) apex of penis; (I) tegmen, lateral view; (J) tegmen, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5200509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5200509/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1912">Figure 3F–J</figureCitation>
